 34/// Provide an operation-specific backend list.
 35template <typename O> struct List;
 36
 37template <typename O,                               // operation
 38          typename S = typename Signature<O>::type, // signature
 39          typename L = typename List<O>::type,      // list of backends
 40          typename B = typename L::first,           // current backend
 41          typename N = typename L::rest,            // the remainder of the list
 42          typename E = Evaluator<O, B, S>,          // the current evaluator
 43          bool V = E::ct_valid>
 44struct Dispatcher;
 45
 46/// If ct-check fails, move to next in the list.
 47template <typename O, typename S, typename L, typename B, typename N, typename E>
 48struct Dispatcher<O, S, L, B, N, E, false> : Dispatcher<O, S, N> {};
 49
 50template <typename O, typename S>
 51struct No_backend_available_for;
 52
 53template <typename O, typename S, typename L, typename B, typename E>
 54struct Dispatcher<O, S, L, B, None_type, E, false>
 55  : No_backend_available_for<O, S> 
 56{};
 57
 58/// Specialization for compile-time only checking. Instead of a full signature,
 59/// it takes a type parameter directly. Thus it would be accessed as
 60/// e.g 'Dispatcher<Operation, float>::type'.
 61template <typename O,
 62          typename T,
 63          typename L, typename B, typename N, typename E>
 64struct Dispatcher<O, T, L, B, N, E, true>
 65{
 66  typedef B backend;
 67  typedef typename E::backend_type type;
 68};
 69
 70/// General case for R(A).
 71template <typename O,
 72          typename R, typename A,
 73          typename L, typename B, typename N, typename E>
 74struct Dispatcher<O, R(A), L, B, N, E, true>
 75{
 76  typedef B backend;
 77  typedef typename Profile_policy_selector<O, R(A), B>::type profiler_type;
 78
 79  static R dispatch(A a)
 80  {
 81    if (E::rt_valid(a))
 82    {
 83      profiler_type profiler(a);
 84      return E::exec(a);
 85    }
 86    else return Dispatcher<O, R(A), N>::dispatch(a);
 87  }
 88};
 89
 90/// Terminator for R(A): If rt-check fails, give up.
 91template <typename O, typename R, typename A, typename L, typename B, typename E>
 92struct Dispatcher<O, R(A), L, B, None_type, E, true>
 93{
 94  typedef B backend;
 95  typedef typename Profile_policy_selector<O, R(A), B>::type profiler_type;
 96
 97  static R dispatch(A a)
 98  {
 99    if (E::rt_valid(a))
100    {
101      profiler_type profiler(a);
102      return E::exec(a);
103    }
104    else VSIP_IMPL_THROW(impl::unimplemented("No backend"));
105  }
106};

396template <typename O, typename R, typename A>
397R dispatch(A a) 
398{
399  typedef dispatcher::Dispatcher<O, R(A)> dispatcher_type;
400  return dispatcher_type::dispatch(a);
401}

403template <typename O, typename R, typename A1, typename A2>
404R dispatch(A1 a1, A2 a2) 
405{ 
406  typedef dispatcher::Dispatcher<O, R(A1, A2)> dispatcher_type;
407  return dispatcher_type::dispatch(a1, a2);
408}
